Dear members of the Selection Committee,

\

It is with pleasure that I provide my support for Dr. Harrison Hsiang's application to the MGH T32 Training Program in Precision & Genomic Medicine. I am enthusiastic about the opportunity to serve as his mentor, should he be selected for the program.

Dr. Hsiang is a current postdoctoral fellow in the Lopez Laboratory for Regenerative Cellular Therapy in the Department of Neurosurgery at MGH, where his work centers on developing and applying precise gene editing and cellular reprogramming strategies to cell replacement therapy in Parkinson's disease. He brings with him a strong background studying Parkinson's disease alongside scientific rigor, curiosity, and dedication to his research. I am confident that his background and skill set will enable him to excel as a program participant.

As a mentor, I am committed to supporting Dr. Hsiang's scientific and professional development through the T32 training program. I will work closely with him to ensure that his training plan aligns with the goals of the program and prepares him for a successful career as an independent scientist in precision and genomic medicine.

I fully support Dr. Hsiang's application and would be pleased to serve as his mentor. Please feel free to contact me should any additional information be required.

\

Sincerely, 

*Ben R. Kleinstiver, PhD*

Associate Professor of Pathology \
Harvard Medical School 

Associate Investigator \ 
Kayden-Lambert MGH Research Scholar \
Massachusetts General Hospital
